Past Senior Special Assistant, SSA’s and Special Advisers, (SA) Wednesday declared to ensure that the All Progressive Congress, APC candidate, Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu emerged victorious in September Governorship election in the state. They explained that their decision to resign their appointment from Governor Godwin Obaseki’s administration was as a result of what they described as the negative attitude of the governor. Convener of the group, Comrade Solomon Okoduwa, said the APC candidate has shown commitment and strength of character in developing the state. The group in a statement also condemned the attack by the governor and his hireling on eminent citizens of the state noting that the campaign to maligned Capt Hosa Okunbo and Comrade Adams Oshiomhole is the height of ingratitude. “We endorsed the APC candidate, Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu. He is a man who has lived all his life in Edo state and understand the problem of his people. He is accessible, reliable and dependable. “We want to also use this medium to condemn the onslaught against our illustrious son, Capt Hosa Okunbo, who had contributed to the growth and development of humanity” 